data.text:
Townhouse Tranquillity In The Sought-After Viewbank College Zone

This tantalising town residence offers plenty of pristinely maintained space along with a quiet location in the keenly sought-after Viewbank College Zone. A quality package for low-maintenance living, it features a well-zoned floor plan with a carpeted lounge, tiled living and dining, open-plan kitchen and an easy-care backyard highlighted by a gazebo allowing for seamless indoor-outdoor entertaining. All three bedrooms are generous in size and share the amenities of a central bathroom and separate toilet. Ideal for downsizers looking to scale down while still residing locally, the home will also appeal to couples, first home buyers, families and investors looking to stake a claim in this tranquil yet ultra-convenient location near the local primary school, shops, transport and open parkland.

• Carpeted formal lounge

• Tiled living/dining with outdoor access via sliding doors

• Open-plan kitchen equipped with gas cooktop, electric oven and Bosch dishwasher

• Laundry with adjoining toilet with basin

• Alfresco deck stepping down to a gazebo covered entertaining courtyard surrounded by easy-care AstroTurf

• Huge main bedroom with built-in robes

• Two more generously sized bedrooms with built-in robes

• Family bathroom with bath, separate shower and separate toilet with basin

• Single garage with internal entry

• Under-stair storage

• Ducted gas heating

• Evaporative cooling

• High hedged fences promoting privacy

Quiet location in the exclusive Viewbank College Zone and close to Viewbank Primary School, Rosanna Train Station, bus stops, Diamond Village Shopping Centre, Castleton Park, Price Park, Banyule Flats Reserve, the Plenty River Trail, Golf Courses, Watsonia Indoor Pool and main arterials to the Eastern Freeway.
